<subSubSection id="C37B8E8BEB39577AFF6EDA6FFF11FEB5" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDEDD00EB395745FF6EDA6FFCBEF860" blockId="31.[151,1437,1895,2031]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B9150112EB395745FF6EDA6FFEF9F828" bold="true" box="[151,274,1895,1922]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Arista with 1 or 2 ventral branches (ch.6-1); posterior postgonite present only on right side of aedeagal sheath, short, apically blunt, and left lateral lobe long, broad, somewhat sinuated, apically with very large, trifurcated, anterior postgonite (“Figs 17, 18” in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0A0F1EB395745FD84DAB8FCA2F860" author="Chen" box="[637,841,1967,1995]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="419 - 429" refId="ref34109" refString="Chen, H. W., Toda, M. J. &amp; Gao, J. J. (2005 b) The Phortica (s. str.) foliiseta species-complex (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from China and its adjacent countries. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30, 419 - 429." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B9150112EB395745FD46DAB9FD1BF860" box="[703,752,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. 2005b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDEDD00EB39577AFF3EDADBFD07FF7D" blockId="31.[151,1437,1895,2031]" lastBlockId="32.[151,1437,153,324]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B9150112EB395745FF3EDADBFDE1F844" bold="true" box="[199,522,2003,2030]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Supplementary description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName id="4C61A683EB395745FC52DADDFBB7F844" authorityName="Gong, Zhu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[939,1116,2004,2031]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangyuanae">
<emphasis id="B9150112EB395745FC52DADDFC57F844" box="[939,956,2005,2030]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9150112EB395745FC31DADCFBB7F844" box="[968,1116,2004,2030]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">zhangyuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 20–22. Apical, leaf-like expansion of arista apically pointed or with minute, awn-like projection. Cibarial, medial sensilla 7–8 per side. All tarsi with gray tarsomeres IV and V.
</paragraph>
